  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nUser requested testing of Webflow connector capabilities, then pivoted to creating a static photo gallery website. Manus designed and built 'Lumina', a professional photo gallery with black/violet cyberpunk aesthetics, featuring categorized albums, lightbox viewing, and mobile upload functionality. The project demonstrates web development capabilities rather than Webflow connector usage.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nInitial intent was to test and demonstrate Webflow MCP connector features. User then requested a practical photo gallery website with mobile upload capability and specific design requirements.\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nCreated a complete static photo gallery website called 'Lumina' with professional cyberpunk design, masonry grid layout, categorized albums, lightbox functionality, and mobile-optimized upload interface with QR code capability.\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [website] Lumina Photo Gallery — Static website with black/violet theme, categorized photo albums, and mobile upload UI\n- [design_concept] Nocturnal Neon Design — Cyberpunk minimalism design system with specific color palette and typography choices\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Selected static over dynamic website approach\n- Chose 'Nocturnal Neon' cyberpunk design theme\n- Implemented masonry grid with lightbox for optimal photo viewing\n- Created mobile-first upload interface with QR code integration\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Cyberpunk design aesthetic matched user requirements\n- Mobile-first upload approach addressed phone-to-web workflow\nFailed / suboptimal:\n\n- Webflow connector testing was abandoned in favor of custom development\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Static websites can support sophisticated photo gallery features with proper design\n\n## Challenges & Blockers\n\n- Static website limitation prevents real photo storage without backend\n- QR code functionality requires live deployment to generate working links\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- How to implement actual photo persistence in static environment?\n- What backend solution would best support mobile photo uploads?\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Implement backend integration for cloud storage and database\n- Deploy website to public domain for QR code functionality\n- Add social sharing features to lightbox viewer\n---\nUID: bT7srwVDo4EPasPbu8VwRn | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0146\n"
